  "market_context": "Gold formed a 2 AM London reversal on the 4-hour chart, setting up an anticipated 6 AM continuation candle expected to make its high early, respect the previous candle's equilibrium, and then expand lower.",
  "key_observation": "By dropping to the 3-minute fractal model, the analyst confirmed the formation of the 4-hour wick via a consolidation high sweep and change in state of delivery, allowing a positional short entry at the 6 AM open targeting -1 standard deviation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified a 2 AM London reversal on the 4-hour gold chart, projecting a bearish continuation for the 6 AM candle.",
    "Defined the ideal 6 AM profile: price opens, makes a high while respecting previous candle EQ, then trades lower — goal is to let the wick form and trade the body.",
    "Dropped to the 3-minute time frame to find a fractal model that aligns with the anticipated 4-hour wick.",
    "Observed price forming a consolidation and noted the need to sweep the consolidation highs while still respecting EQ.",
    "Waited for the consolidation high to be run out, then required a change in state of delivery to confirm the reversal point.",
    "Confirmed the closure through the opposing candle series; identified a candle 3 closure on the 30-minute forming a protected swing right before the new 4-hour open.",
    "Marked 50% of the change in state of delivery and the opposing 30-minute candle as invalidation — price could trade into but not above this area.",
    "Took a positional entry at the open of the new 4-hour candle with stop on the protected swing, targeting 2R / -1 standard deviation.",
    "Observed price falling just short of 2R into a fair value gap; outlined that a continuation entry would require a new protected swing and a second confirmation.",
    "Got the second confirmation, which served as a continuation entry; price expanded lower and the 6 AM 4-hour candle closed as an expansion candle with a small wick and large body."
  ],
  "outcome": "Initial positional entry fell just shy of the 2R target before retracing into a fair value gap; a continuation entry on the second confirmation then captured the expansion lower, with the 6 AM 4-hour candle closing as a small-wick, large-body expansion candle.",
  "lessons": "The GXT model uses a lower time frame fractal entry (3-minute consolidation sweep + CISD) to confirm formation of a higher time frame candle's wick, allowing precise positional entry at the new HTF candle open with tight risk and 2R+ potential into standard deviation targets.",
